AN open day is to be held to provide information about major works planned for the Raith Junction on the M74.The will see the creation of an underpass below the existing roundabout, providing a link for traffic between the Bellshill Bypass and the East Kilbride Expressway.The improvements at Raith Junction will require speed restrictions, temporary lane closures and diversions, to allow excavation works to start.An informal drop-in day event will take place from 12 noon to 8pm at the Holiday Inn Express, Strathclyde Country Park on Thursday May 21 providing residents with the opportunity to view the contractors plans of the new road layout and provide an overview of the construction works scheduled for the months ahead.